Amendment No. 2 to HJR1479
Jones J
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND < S B> House Joint Resolution No. 1479*
by inserting the following immediately after the fourth WHEREAS clause:
WHEREAS, Carnton Plantation was constructed and maintained largely through the
labor of enslaved people. In 1860, the McGavock family enslaved forty-four people, who
worked the land and lived under the threat of violence and separation. These enslaved persons
endured systematic oppression, including hard labor, forced relocation to Alabama during the
Civil War, and separation from their loved ones. The brutal system of slavery at Carnton
Plantation was also maintained through surveillance and control. Mariah Reddick, an enslaved
woman, served as Carrie McGavock's body servant, a role that meant being constantly
available to the plantation owners; and
